  "prompt": "What are the advantages and disadvantages of limited liability company?",
  "response": "Here are the advantages and disadvantages of a Limited Liability Company (LLC):\n\nAdvantages:\n1. Personal Asset Protection\n- Members' personal assets are protected\n- Limited liability for business debts and legal actions\n\n2. Tax Flexibility\n- Can choose pass-through taxation\n- Option to be taxed as corporation or partnership\n- Avoid double taxation\n\n3. Management Flexibility\n- Less formal management structure\n- Fewer operational restrictions\n- Flexible profit distribution\n\n4. Easier Formation\n- Simpler registration process\n- Lower startup and maintenance costs\n- Less paperwork compared to corporations\n\n5. Credibility\n- More professional business structure\n- Easier to attract investors\n- Better business perception\n\nDisadvantages:\n1. Higher Costs\n- More expensive to establish than sole proprietorship\n- Annual filing fees\n- Potential state-specific taxes\n\n2. Limited Investment Opportunities\n- Harder to raise capital\n- Restrictions on stock issuance\n- Less attractive to venture capitalists\n\n3. Complex Compliance\n- Different rules in different states\n- Potential complex regulatory requirements\n- More complicated accounting\n\n4. Self-Employment Taxes\n- Members might pay higher self-employment taxes\n- Potentially higher tax burden\n\n5. Limited Lifespan\n- Some jurisdictions require dissolution if member leaves\n- Less permanent than corporations",
